PART-1

# htpasswd -c -B -b </path/to/users.htpasswd> <username> <password>
IF I NEED TO ADD ANOTHER USER THEN I NEED TYPE THIS COMMAND:::------->>>>>>>>>>>>.
####  htpasswd -B -b </path/to/users.htpasswd> <username> <password>  

FOR EXAMPLE:::---->>>
# htpasswd -c -B -b user-details.txt(it could be anything) <username>/ bibek  <password>/ redhat@123

(((((    Use the -c option only when creating a file. The -c option replaces all file content if
the file already exists.)))))

FOR EXAMPLE:::---->>>
# htpasswd -B -b user-details.txt(it could be anything) <username>/ bibek-01  <password>/ redhat@123

PART-2  
Creating HTPASWD secret:::::------------->>>>

# oc create secret generic htpass-secret --from-file=htpasswd=<path_to_users.htpasswd> -n openshift-config 
///// oc create secret generic htpass-secret --from-file=htpasswd=<path_to_users.htpasswd> -n openshift-config

## oc edit secret/htpass-secret   hit enter
## oc extract secret/htpass-secret -to=-

#####   oc create secret generic htpass-secret --from-file=htpasswd=<path_to_users.htpasswd> /user-details.txt -n openshift-config ######
