PART-3 
NOW LET'S CONFIURE OAUTH AUTHENTICATION:::::::--------------------->>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
## oc get oauth
## oc get oauth/cluster
FOR BACKUP::>>
## oc get oauth/cluster -oyaml > oauth-backup.yaml
## oc edit oauth OR  ## oc edit oauth/cluster 
##  oc get secret -n openshift-config

{{{{{{{   Main Purpose of openshift-config

The namespace is used for storing:
 Identity provider configuration

HTPasswd secret

LDAP certificates

GitHub OAuth secrets

OAuth client secrets}}}}}}}}}


## watch oc get po -n openshift-authentication

{{{{{{{{{ 1. oauth-openshift pods

These pods implement the OAuth server for OpenShift.
They handle:

Login pages
Identity provider flows (HTPasswd, LDAP, GitHub, Google, etc.)
Token requests
Logout requests.

2. authentication-operator pod

Ensures OAuth server is running correctly.
Watches changes in the openshift-config namespace.
Reconciles OAuth configuration continuously.}}}}}}}}}}}



